items.name: Marisha Ray

LyCORIS of Marisha Ray

Welcome to my corner!

I'm creating Dreambooths, LyCORIS, and LORAs. If you want to know how I do those, here is the guide: https://civitai.com/articles/7/dreambooth-lycoris-lora-guide

items.name: Nunnu („Å¨„Çì„Å¨) - Artist Style
items.description:
If you enjoyed this model, why don't you check out my other works? I put a lot of effort into correctly recreating artist styles and making the occasional character LoRA.üòä

This model was trained using the collab/guide by holostrawberry [Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free - colabs | Stable Diffusion Other | Civitai

The versions were selected based on testing in AOM3. I recommend experimenting with the weights when using other checkpoints.

Edit:

It was brought to my attention that there is a pretty big disconnect between AOM and NAI. While I will not rework this model in the foreseeable future, gen22 works surprisingly well on NAI and doesn't feel particularly overbaked. Checkpoints built on NAI like Anything should therefore use gen22.

About the artist:

Twitter: „Å¨„Çì„Å¨ (@nunnu_zero) / Twitter

Nunnu creates hentai and unsurprisingly the model will favor nsfw image generation.

Expect large eyes, stray hair locks and smooth feeling characters.

Weights & Prompts

AOM3:

Use a weight of 1.0, adjust to taste. This model is flexible and compatible with other LoRA (character or pose models) at full weight. As usual I have included an XYZ plot for reference.

Old Gen:

Originally I trained on NAI instead of on AOM3. The attempt to make the model useable with different checkpoints diluted the style and introduced some problems.

Most colored images by Nunnu depict one of two characters, which means that among other things hair color tends towards one of two choices (white and brown).

Gen 15:

Use a weight of 1.0.

Gen 22:

Use a weight of 0.7-1.0. This gen gets a lot closer to the original style but is overbaked.

For reference most image prompts were reused.

Please leave a review if you enjoyed this model or have problems with it. This helps me with improving future models and finetuning them in general. Give it a try and throw some images down below! üëá

items.name: Lee Marvin Lora
items.description:
First of all, model is for fun. Make cool images, make Lee Marvin as Superman, make him as a silly clown, whatever. No selling, no gross stuff. Be nice. Be kind. Be smart and be respectful!

Starting to make LORAs of cult actors and more obscure figures for Civitai. Far too many beautiful actresses and waifus! Time for when men where men, life was hard and everyone died from alcoholism at 55!

Lora works best with cyberrealistic, but is pretty versatile. I have all ten epochs but am uploading the one I use most. If you would like the others just comment and I can upload it.

Lee Marvin (February 19, 1924¬†‚Äì August 29, 1987) was an American film and television actor. Known for his bass voice and premature white hair, he is best remembered for playing hardboiled "tough guy" characters. Although initially typecast as the "heavy" (i.e. villainous character), he later gained prominence for portraying anti-heroes, such as Detective Lieutenant Frank Ballinger on the television series M Squad (1957‚Äì1960). Marvin's notable roles in film included Charlie Strom in The Killers (1964), Rico Fardan in The Professionals (1966), Major John Reisman in The Dirty Dozen (1967), Ben Rumson in Paint Your Wagon (1969), Walker in Point Blank (1967), and the Sergeant in The Big Red One (1980).

Marvin achieved numerous accolades when he portrayed both gunfighter Kid Shelleen and criminal Tim Strawn in a dual role for the comedy Western film Cat Ballou (1965), alongside Jane Fonda, a surprise hit which won him the Academy Award for Best Actor, along with a BAFTA Award, a Golden Globe Award, an NBR Award, and the Silver Bear for Best Actor.

items.name: Kiyomi Pyon-Pyon (Kiki)
items.description:
Overview

Kiyomi Pyon-Pyon (Kiki) LoRA trained on images and fanarts of her.

Just use V2.0 or DICE version, they're more stable than previous ones.

Using the model

Use "four-leaf clover hairclip" to summon her hairclip. V1.1 for some reason enforces this (as in "you have to add it").

Sometimes the model requires some guidance, so add "ears", "black shirt", "off shoulder", and "long hair" or "low twintails".

On V2.0 and DICE, elf ears or cat ears may appear, so add "pointy ears, cat ears" to the negative prompt.

Model details

  • V1: Base model for the anime art style, trained on fanarts. Should only be used for merging.

  • V1.1: Merge of V1 and another model that was trained on screenshots and Dongus' artworks. Improves hair clip consistency.

  • V2.0: Merge of 2 retrained models with better tagging and V1. Handles outfits better.

  • DICE: Merge of V2.0 and /pyon/ anon's V2.2 model. Should run as good as the anon's model on many checkpoints while retaining some of my models style.

items.description:
This is a new set of pistol holding poses to the collection. This set contains a total of 44 different kind of pistol holding poses, each pose has been captured from 25 different angles, giving you a wide range of options.

Please keep in mind that due to the more dynamic poses or camera angles, some images may need to be resized to fit your specific needs.

All the images in the set are in png format with the background removed, making it possible to use multiple images in a single scene without worrying about overlapping backgrounds. Additionally, the Controlnet system does not require a background to use the images, so they can be imported as they are.

If you want to be more safe on the image generation with poses, you can use any image editing software to add the black background on the back of the poses.

Creating these pose sets takes a lot of time and effort, any donation will help me to continue creating more pose sets in the future. Thank you :)

items.name: Zeroscope V2 576w (txt2video)
items.description:
Stop! These models are not for txt2img inference!

Don't put them in your stable-diffusion-webui/models directory and expect to make images!

So what are these?

These are new Modelscope based models for txt2video, optimized to produce 16:9 video compositions. They've been trained on 9,923 video clips and 29,769 tagged frames at 24 fps, 576x320 res.

Note that they can look much better - I had to convert the mp4 outputs to gif for Civitai. We can also upscale these videos using the Zeroscope v2 XL txt2vid models, which I'm currently uploading!

Note: this model is the lighter version of the XL model (available here) which requires a lot more VRAM. If you have >15GB of VRAM, you should be using the XL version.

Where do they go?

Drop them in the \stable-diffusion-webui\models\ModelScope\t2v folder

It's imperative you rename the text2video_pytorch_model.pt to .pth extension after downloading.

The files must be named open_clip_pytorch_model.bin, and text2video_pytorch_model.pth

Who made them? Original Source?

https://huggingface.co/cerspense/zeroscope_v2_576w

What else do I need?

These models are specifically for use with the txt2video Auto1111 WebUI Extension

items.name: Toxic Avenger
items.description:
‚ÄúMelvin you're beautiful. You're a beautiful person. You're so muscular. It's been two years since I've touched a man.‚Äù

If you like my contributions to the community, please consider Buying Me A Coffee or check out my other sites on AllMyLinks

TRAINING INFO

  • Trained on 26 photos (face & full body)

  • Trained at 512 resolution

RECOMMENDED SETTINGS

PROMPTS - "Mop", "from behind", "growling" and others are trained into the Lora. For a full list of the prompts/captioned used for training, check the Lora file's metadata in your webgui

WEIGHT - A weight of 0.6-0.8 will give the best mix of likeness and flexibility.

FACE RESTORATION - Leave it off since Toxie is already perfect.

GETTING THE BEST LIKENESS WITH LORA'S

The checkpoint you use can heavily influence the likeness of a celebrity Lora. I train my Lora's on SD15, so you'll get the best likeness on any model that used SD15 as the base model. See this example for how a checkpoint can influence the look of a Lora.

items.name: Avril Lavigne (2000s)
items.description:
Avril Ramona Lavigne (born September 27, 1984) is a Canadian singer and songwriter.

Please provide constructive criticism.

You can support me here to be able to render better models (https://ko-fi.com/djo226). Supporters can request model.

Prompt : Lavigne, realistic, natural lighting, post-processing, ultra realistic, highly detailed, very detailed, cinematic, hyper realistic, intricate scenery, sharp, photo by Annie Leibovitz, film, studio lighting, detailed skin, ultra realistic, bokeh, sharp features <lora:Lavigne:0.8>

Negative prompt: (deformed iris, deformed pupils, semi-realistic, cgi, 3d, render, sketch, cartoon, drawing, anime, mutated hands and fingers:1.4), (deformed, distorted, disfigured:1.3), poorly drawn, bad anatomy, wrong anatomy, extra limb, missing limb, floating limbs, disconnected limbs, mutation, mutated, ugly, disgusting, amputation

Steps: 90, Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras, CFG scale: 12, Seed: -1, Face restoration: GFPGAN, Size: 768x1024, Model hash: 81086e2b3f, Model: realisticVisionV20_v20

Face restoration is optional, may provide better result if not activated.

Use Lavigne as trigger.

New process to get better result :

Set a prompt with a low weight (like <lora:Lavigne:0.4>) and the action/situation you want (even with a lower resolution like 512x768, it'll be faster and avoid duplicate). Send the result of your choice to img2img, set the weight to <lora:Lavigne:0.9>, set a higher resolution but keep proportion. Enjoy!

items.name: Ava from "Ex Machina" (2014)
items.description:
Ex Machina is a 2014 science fiction psychological thriller film written and directed by Alex Garland in his directorial debut. A co-production between the United Kingdom and the United States, it stars Domhnall Gleeson, Alicia Vikander (as Ava), and Oscar Isaac. It follows a programmer who is invited by his CEO to administer the Turing test to an intelligent humanoid robot.

Please provide constructive criticism.

You can support me here to be able to render better models (https://ko-fi.com/djo226). Supporters can request model.

Prompt : Ava, a robot, realistic, natural lighting, post-processing, ultra realistic, highly detailed, very detailed, cinematic, hyper realistic, intricate scenery, sharp, photo by Annie Leibovitz, film, studio lighting, detailed skin, ultra realistic, bokeh, sharp features <lora:Ava:0.8>

Negative prompt: (deformed iris, deformed pupils, semi-realistic, cgi, 3d, render, sketch, cartoon, drawing, anime, mutated hands and fingers:1.4), (deformed, distorted, disfigured:1.3), poorly drawn, bad anatomy, wrong anatomy, extra limb, missing limb, floating limbs, disconnected limbs, mutation, mutated, ugly, disgusting, amputation

Steps: 90, Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras, CFG scale: 12, Seed: -1, Face restoration: GFPGAN, Size: 768x1024, Model hash: 81086e2b3f, Model: realisticVisionV20_v20

Face restoration is optional, may provide better result if not activated.

Use Ava, a robot as trigger. You can add bald, no hair if you get any.

New process to get better result :

Set a prompt with a low weight (like <lora:Ava:0.4>) and the action/situation you want (even with a lower resolution like 512x768, it'll be faster and avoid duplicate). Send the result of your choice to img2img, set the weight to <lora:Ava:0.9>, set a higher resolution but keep proportion. Enjoy!

items.name: Ferania (Deathblight) Crescentia Fortuna's Character LoRA
items.description:
Crescentia's character from the Deathblight webcomic the Wolf Girl Ferania. Works well on 0.6-1.0 training done on NAI.

Trigger: "Ferania" is needed always.

Outfits:

  • Classic: "red shirt, bare shoulders, cleavage cutout, fingerless gloves, black gloves, elbow gloves, belt, black skirt, fur collar"

  • Casual: "choker, fur trim, black jacket, red crop top, black gloves, belt, black miniskirt"

The outfits are a bit inconsistent due to the data available being limited but hold up pretty well all things considered. "Fingerless gloves" have a tendency not to work well as I had to remove them manually from the data as they were causing extra broken finger generation.

Recommended: "red eyes, red lips" if the eyes/lips decide to change colour. Depending on pose/models sometimes the "wolf ears, wolf tail" may not show up so add the tags to fix. Sometimes abs can generate funny and I find adding "navel" helps improve quality.

This LoRa was a journey with many issues caused by red nails and fingerless gloves of all things but I am really happy with how it turned out so I hope you all enjoy it. For anybody who enjoys this comic I plan to try and make some more characters from it alongside other lesser known characters that also deserve a LoRA.

Feedback and reviews are always appreciated.

items.name: Spa Style
items.description:
This is a New scenery / building Style Lora I have created, it is suitable for 2d style generations.

I will suggest using between 0.5 to 0.8 weight for this Lora. Using weight above 0.8 can look more like the art style however it could have the over trained effect and messy.

This Lora is trained on a lot of digital painted scenery / building in certain style, not sure if it works on characters, you can try.

Model: Most known models

Example positive prompt

(space), (universe), (galaxy), stars, milky way, (planets), black hole, (accretion disk), crane_(machine), mecha, castle, robot, scenery, science_fiction, labcoat, cable, monitor, screen, buildings, wide shot, scenery, aircraft, military_vehicle, (halo), airplane, vehicle_focus, spacecraft, (no name), (no signatures)

Example 2

forest, trees, crane_(machine), mecha, castle, robot, scenery, science_fiction, labcoat, cable, monitor, screen, buildings, wide shot, scenery, aircraft, military_vehicle, (halo), airplane, vehicle_focus, spacecraft, (no name), (no signatures)

Example 3

water, crane_(machine), mecha, castle, robot, scenery, science_fiction, no human, cable, monitor, screen, buildings, wide shot, scenery, underwater, (halo), airplane, vehicle_focus, spacecraft, (no name), (no signatures)

For negative prompts I will suggest using the popular or well known negative embeddings that are available in the Civitai site.

items.name: Zeroscope V2 XL (txt2video)
items.description:
Stop! These models are not for txt2img inference!

Don't put them in your stable-diffusion-webui/models directory and expect to make images!

So what are these?

These are new Modelscope based models for txt2video, optimized to produce 16:9 video compositions. They've been trained on 9,923 video clips and 29,769 tagged frames at 24 fps, 1024x576 res.

Note that these are the bigger brothers to the https://civitai.com/models/96454/zeroscope-v2-576w-txt2video models. The XL models use 15.3GB of VRAM when rendering 30 fps at 1024x576.

Where do they go?

Drop them in the \stable-diffusion-webui\models\ModelScope\t2v folder

It's imperative you rename the text2video_pytorch_model.pt to .pth extension after downloading.

The files must be named open_clip_pytorch_model.bin, and text2video_pytorch_model.pth

Who made them? Original Source?

https://huggingface.co/cerspense/zeroscope_v2_XL

What else do I need?

These models are specifically for use with the txt2video Auto1111 WebUI Extension

items.name: Klaus Kinski Lora
items.description:
First of all, model is for fun. Make cool images, make Klaus Kinski as The Joker, make him as a a pirate, whatever. No selling, no gross stuff. Be nice. Be kind. Be smart and be respectful!

Typically works best with prompts starting with "kk1, man, solo, blank blank blank" and then add "<lora:KlausKinski-06:1>" at the end. Lora works best with cyberrealistic, but is pretty versatile. I have all ten epochs but am uploading the one I use most. If you would like the others just comment and I can upload it.

Part of an ongoing to make LORAs of cult actors and more obscure figures for Civitai. Far too many beautiful actresses and waifus! Time for when men where men, life was hard and everyone died from alcoholism at 55!

Klaus Kinski (German: [kla äs Ààk…™nskiÀê] (listen), born Klaus G√ºnter Karl Nakszynski[2] 18 October 1926 ‚Äì 23 November 1991)[3] was a German actor,[4] equally renowned for his intense performance style and notorious for his volatile personality.[5][6][7] He appeared in over 130 film roles in a career that spanned 40 years, from 1948 to 1988. He played leading parts in five films directed by Werner Herzog (Aguirre, the Wrath of God, 1972; Nosferatu the Vampyre, 1979; Woyzeck, also 1979; Fitzcarraldo, 1982; Cobra Verde, 1987), who later chronicled their tumultuous relationship in the documentary My Best Fiend (1999).[8]

Kinski's roles spanned multiple genres, languages, and nationalities, including many Spaghetti Westerns (such as For a Few Dollars More, 1965; A Bullet for the General, 1966; The Great Silence, 1968; And God Said to Cain, 1970), horror films, war movies, dramas, and Edgar Wallace krimi pictures. His infamy was elevated by a number of eccentric creative endeavors, including a one-man show based on the life of Jesus Christ,[9] a self-directed biographical film of violinist Niccol√≤ Paganini, and over 20 spoken word albums.[10]
